      • send

        public void send(Packet packet)
        Description copied from class: OutputPort
        Send a packet to this Port. The thread is suspended if no capacity is currently available. If the port or connection has been closed, false is returned; otherwise, true is returned.

        Do not reference the packet after sending - someone else may be modifying it!

        Overrides:

      • close

        public void close()
        Description copied from class: OutputPort
        Close this OutputPort. This is a signal that no further packets will be sent via this OutputPort. Since more than one OutputPort may feed a given Connection, this does not necessarily close the Connection.
